A rare sight on most worlds, these missile silos are dug deep into the ground to protect them from prying eyes. As strategic weapons, they often form the first response to planetary invasions and as such are often extensively searched for by spies and clandestine raiders before any drop ships breach atmosphere.

At normalK scale, it measures 150mm square, comes both solid and hollowed with ~2.00 walls. Epic scale has some finer details removed for ease of printing and supporting.

A 1/5th resizing of all previously released M'khand Pattern Heavy Tank Turret & Weapons files, plus large speakers, decals and a variety of commander's hatch. Ideal for uparming epic scale lemoine russel battle tanks, or fitting onto epic scale fortified anti-air emplacements or epic scale M'khand Pattern HDC Heavy Tanks.

Some details have been altered or removed to ensure proper printing at this size. 3.5x1.25mm holes are included for magnetising turrets to tank hulls.

The zip includes the meshmixer fils which can have any other epic scale lemoine russel variants placed in to maximise the use of said parts. Simply Shift+Click the pieces you want to use and select export under the FILE dropdown menu. Alternatively, parts can be assembled via 3dBuilder or another software of your choice. Exported pieces are then ready for repair in netfab/3dbuilder/prusaslicer and slicing.

The All-Purpose Carrier lives up to its name as a rugged and dependable platform that has been adapted to almost every role on & off the battlefield.

This all-in-one package of M'khand-pattern All-Purpose Carrier parts allows you to build your ideal APC-based vehicle to your exact needs. Contains all previously released APC-chassis related files***, both free and paid, adapted to 1:300 scale for mass-scale wargames.

Turrets and middles have 2.5x1.25mm holes for magnets. Compatible with all epic scale M'khand-pattern APC & Lemoine Russel turrets.

To use meshmixer builder, open with meshmixer (a free program from autodesk) and ctrl-click in the object browser the items you wish to have as one piece. Then go to File and Export. Your merged piece is ready for repair and slicing.

Alternatively, individual part stls can be assembled in 3Dbuilder or another program of your choice where they should snap together.

***Non-IFV turrets, Christie suspension sides and artillery cannons for unarmoured hulls not included***

An improved pattern of the M'khand Pattern Lemoine Russel Battle Tank, with improved suspension and internal layout offering more crew comfort and higher accuracy when firing on the move. Comes with all turret coxial and sponson weapon options offered at larger scales for maximum customisation.

Completed bodies, turrets and middles have 2.5x1.25mm holes for magnets. Compatible with all epic scale M'khand-pattern Lemoine Russel parts and variants. Comes with a variety of decals and effects.

The zip includes all my parts and meshmixer files. With Meshmixer (free program from Autodesk), simply Shift+Click the pieces you want to use and select export under the FILE dropdown menu. Alternatively, parts can be assembled via 3dBuilder, Blender or another software of your choice. Exported pieces are then ready for repair in netfab/3dbuilder/prusaslicer and slicing.

For best results when printing destroyed turrets, include a closed hatch with the turret, weapon and smoke to prevent a small pocket of unprinted resin.

__For printing for LIMP/AT18, increase scale to 125% when slicing__

2023-12-03: Added new options for side weapons and a builder with all my other lemoine russel variants in it.

2023-12-07: Added adapters to fit the turrets to plastic LIMP hulls. Combine with other wanted parts before scaling up 125%

2023-12-07: Split hull weapon mounts from the hulls. Added new hull weapon options. Removed the old redundant builder file.

2024-01-14: Added coronal-designations of the three patterns of turret as well as both a turret-mounted heat ray and heavy flamethrower.

2024-08-24: Added internal side sponsons.
